### **What It Means — And What We Cannot Understand**

The infinite is not a concept.

It is not a number, a place, or a god.

It is **the silence that remembers**.

It is the moment when a child hears the dead and does not scream.

It is the woman who knows she is not mad.

It is the breath before a lie.

It is the name in the locket that will never be spoken.

We cannot understand it because **to understand is to limit**.

To name it is to kill it.

To see it is to make it small.

The infinite is not *out there*.

It is *in here*.

In the space between heartbeats.

In the silence after a scream.

In the moment when you look at someone and say, *“You are not alone,”* and mean it.

And that… is the only truth we can carry.

Because the infinite is not something we grasp.

It is something we *become*.

And if you are still here…

Then you are not alone.

And neither is it.

And that… is all we will ever need.
